---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '@components/Hero.astro';
import PillarGrid from '@components/PillarGrid.astro';
import CTA from '@components/CTA.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Pulse & Heritage">
  <Hero
    eyebrow="Health equity, written by a clinician who lived it"
    headline="Because everyone deserves to be seen, heard, and treated appropriately."
    subhead="Pulse & Heritage is health equity content for veterans and people of color — written by an AANP board-certified Family Nurse Practitioner and U.S. combat veteran. Clinically precise. Universally clear."
    ctaLabel="Read the latest"
    ctaHref="/articles/"
    secondaryCtaLabel="Meet Allison"
    secondaryCtaHref="/about/"
  />

  <section class="py-20 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-pulse-600 mb-4">
      Why this exists
    </p>
    <p
      class="text-2xl md:text-3xl text-heritage-900 leading-snug"
      style="font-family: var(--font-serif);"
    >
      In high-acuity care — ICU, oncology, cardiac procedures — and in a VA
      clinic seeing veterans manage complex conditions, the same patterns
      surfaced. Who gets heard. Who gets dismissed. Whose pain is taken
      seriously. Whose symptoms are explained away. These patterns are most
      visible at the intersection of race, background, and military service.
      This site exists to name them — and to put practical tools in the hands
      of the people the system most often fails.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-6 text-base text-ink-600 italic">
      — Allison Smith, MSN, FNP-C
    </p>
  </section>

  <PillarGrid />

  <CTA
    headline="Get the next piece in your inbox."
    body="No spam, no sales funnels. Just clinical clarity, plainly written, when there's something worth reading."
    ctaLabel="Subscribe"
    ctaHref="/subscribe/"
    variant="heritage"
  />
</BaseLayout>
